   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FOURTEEN THE SENSE OF THE SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND KNOWING THE SPIRIT 1 Scripture Reading: Rom 8:2, 6 OUTLINE Four things: Life v. 2a: The Spirit of life.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Spirit containing life and belonging to life.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Spirit being the source of life and life being the issue of the Spirit v. 6b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Law v. 2a: The Spirit not only belonging to life but also having its law.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Life being the content and issue of the Spirit; law of life being the function and action of the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>By contacting life we touch the spirit; by sensing the law we also sense the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Peace v. 6b: Peace being also the issue of the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Touching the spirit, we do not only touch life but also peace.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Death v. 6a: Death being the issue of the flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The sense of death causing us to know the things of the flesh, thus unveiling the spirit from the negative side.</S>
   </TEXT>
